### File Descriptions
```
app.py
- The main backend Python application file.
- Implements the web server, routing, and all business logic for the OnlineLibrary application.
- Handles reading from and writing to the local text files in the 'data' directory.
- Manages user sessions, page rendering, and data processing for all functionalities (search, borrow, return, reviews, reservations, payments, profile management).
- Using a single backend file is feasible given the moderate complexity and local file storage.

requirements.txt
- Lists Python dependencies required to run the application (e.g., Flask or another lightweight web framework).

README.md
- Provides an overview of the project, setup instructions, and usage notes.

templates/
- Contains all HTML template files for the 10 pages defined in the requirements.
- Each HTML file corresponds to one page (Dashboard, Book Catalog, Book Details, etc.).
- Templates use consistent element IDs as specified for UI components and navigation.

static/
- Contains static assets such as CSS stylesheets, JavaScript files, and images.
- css/styles.css: Styles for the entire web application.
- js/scripts.js: Client-side scripts for UI interactions and dynamic behaviors.
- images/: Stores book cover images and other graphical assets.

data/
- Stores all application data in text files using the specified pipe-delimited format.
- users.txt, books.txt, borrowings.txt, reservations.txt, reviews.txt, fines.txt as per the requirements.
- This directory is read and updated by app.py to persist user and library data.
```
